==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κολοσσός]]''' (''kolossos'') "a very tall man or statue" via {{L.}} ''colossus''.

===Noun===
'''colossus''' (''plural:'' [[colossuses]])

#A statue of gigantic size. The name was especially applied to certain famous statues in antiquity, as the Colossus of Nero in Rome and the [[Colossus of Rhodes]], one of the [[Seven Wonders of the World.]] 
#Any man or beast of gigantic size.

